						<summary>

						<p>Three fragments lying near the Parvatadēva temple (3).</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">11th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This third piece is also broken and is incomplete. It refers to Bhāskara seṭṭi and his construction [of a temple] and installation of the images of gods there in.</p>						

						<p>It is in characters of the 11th century A.D.</p>						

